# {{ project_name }}

A reproducible, governed analysis project run with Claude Code (and Cowork as a thin client).

## Read first, in order

Read these before acting. Stop after each and load only what the task needs.

1. `.claude/constitution.md` — the charter (non-negotiable rules).
2. `.claude/policies/00-index.md` — atomic policies with explicit precedence.
3. `.claude/knowledge-map.md` — the router: task type to the one file to open.
4. `PROJECT_BRIEF.md` — what this specific project is about.

## Do NOT run /init

A curated `CLAUDE.md` is already provided. Running `/init` inflates this file
with auto-discovered noise and rots context over time. Edit this file by hand.

## Companion plugin

Guardrails are NOT defined here. Skills, hooks, and subagents come from the
companion plugin `psotobverse-utils` (orthogonal layer, separate repo). Install it once:

```
/plugin marketplace add psotob91/psotobverse-utils
/plugin install psotobverse-utils@psotobverse-utils
```

The template only references the plugin; it never duplicates its skills, hooks,
or subagents.

## Overlay: generic gate to this project's command

When a workflow expects a generic capability, use the project-specific command below.

| Generic gate            | This project's command            |
|-------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| Tests                   | `make test`                       |
| Linter / format         | `make lint`                       |
| Doc hygiene / index     | `/index` or `/tidy`               |
| Outputs index           | `make reindex`                    |
| Decisions               | `docs/adr/`                       |
| Learning                | `learning/PLAYBOOK.md`            |
| Reproduce env           | `make setup`                      |

## Cowork

Cowork does NOT auto-read this `CLAUDE.md`. Generate `.claude/COWORK_INSTRUCTIONS.md`
with `/sync-cowork` after the first Code session, then paste its block into the
Cowork project's Instructions field.
